Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.30,0:00:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.37,0:00:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's at the top of that hill.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.68,0:00:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.98,0:00:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.77,0:00:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Roses, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.91,0:00:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like the palace in Sleeping Beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.47,0:02:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.67,0:02:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna Liebert.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.80,0:02:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Best of luck, mister great detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.01,0:02:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,She was worried\Nthat something awful might happen to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.91,0:02:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, I feel the same way\Nthat your mother feels.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.45,0:02:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.66,0:02:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you just dreaming,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.36,0:02:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Detective Suk?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.36,0:02:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.23,0:02:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Lunge, an inspector with the BKA.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.17,0:02:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The BKA?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.57,0:02:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay. You can relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.74,0:02:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't come here to arrest you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.21,0:03:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This is quite a nice hospital room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.35,0:03:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to several hospitals\Nwith connections
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.92,0:03:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to the former Czechoslovakia secret police\Nbefore I found you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.59,0:03:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You're being treated quite well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.46,0:03:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be very important\Nto the former secret police.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.23,0:03:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I was simply--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.53,0:03:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I already know all about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.00,0:03:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The beating death of Inspector Zeman who\Nhad connections with the secret police.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.41,0:03:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The poisoning deaths of the commissioner
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.41,0:03:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and two detectives\Nof Prague Police Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.61,0:03:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The shooting deaths of\Nthe two detectives who were tailing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.72,0:03:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You're being pursued as\Na person of interest in all these murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.22,0:03:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Judging from just circumstantial evidence,\Nyou're the murderer in all these cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.63,0:03:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You're wrong.\NI didn't do any of those things!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.70,0:03:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Then was it the tall man, Grimmer,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.60,0:03:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,who Inspector Zeman questioned\Nbefore he was beaten to death?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.24,0:04:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't Mr. Grimmer either!\NHe's not that kind of person!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.71,0:04:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Then who is the murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.05,0:04:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet you know, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.85,0:04:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet you know who the murderer is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.65,0:04:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.36,0:04:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If I knew who it was,\NI wouldn't be in this state.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.49,0:04:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been betrayed over and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.80,0:04:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been framed for murder\Nand the police are after me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.90,0:04:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had enough of this.\NI'm sick of being stabbed in the back!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.41,0:04:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a detective, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.51,0:04:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,As a detective, you must calmly dissect\Nand investigate everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.05,0:04:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Even at the cost of your happiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.85,0:04:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you must keep a level head\Nas you dig up the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.79,0:04:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't want to be betrayed anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.76,0:04:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,then suspect the person\Nyou least want to suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.71,0:05:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Who said you could see him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.19,0:05:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring me to your boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.86,0:05:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell him I want to talk\Nabout the rose mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.20,0:05:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I know he'll want\Nto talk to me about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.34,0:05:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector Lunge of the BKA.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.37,0:05:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I've checked out who you are\Nand about your past.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.94,0:05:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I've also
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.14,0:05:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,heard all kinds of rumors about you\Nduring the old regime, Captain Ranke.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.35,0:05:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard you're\Nalso the de facto leader of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.48,0:05:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the former Czechoslovakia secret police.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.72,0:05:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Things have been quite difficult\Nfor you recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.36,0:05:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.79,0:06:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm envious of people like you\Nwho can take long vacations.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.13,0:06:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that two years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.93,0:06:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,your aggressive investigation of\Nthe secretary of Representative Boltzmann,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.67,0:06:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,a candidate to lead the German\NDemocratic Party, led to his suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.88,0:06:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to be more skillful\Nthan that to get far in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.95,0:06:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You and your people were foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.32,0:06:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If you'd taken a softer line\Nduring democratization
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.72,0:06:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and had managed your secrecy,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.89,0:06:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you could be leading this country now\Nas the shadow president.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.66,0:06:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, the fear that the public has\Nof your people is just an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.24,0:06:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. You're quite sharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.47,0:06:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what brings you and your smarts to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.81,0:06:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,As you already know,\NI'm on an extended vacation,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.61,0:06:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,so I'm partly here for pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.38,0:06:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking for something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.12,0:07:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking for\Nthe embodiment of true fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.66,0:07:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to know if a true demon was born
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.43,0:07:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the illusion\Nthat you people created.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.50,0:07:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is about the Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.58,0:07:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to search quite a lot\Nbefore I found that mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.95,0:07:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because the author of\Nthis book had many pen names.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.99,0:07:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The Nameless Monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.02,0:07:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The author's name is Emil Scherbe
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.79,0:07:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,His address was an apartment\Nin an old building in Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.09,0:07:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,A different company is renting it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.60,0:07:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The address for Klaus Poppe is\Nan old farm house in the suburbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.47,0:07:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's already been torn down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.14,0:07:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Jakob Vyrobek's address is\Nalso just a rental space.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.11,0:07:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But you eventually found…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.88,0:07:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz Bonaparta?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.58,0:08:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it with that mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.35,0:08:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is Franz Bonaparta?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.09,0:08:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how much I search,\NI can't find anything on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.56,0:08:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Which can only mean\Nthat he was one of your people,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.43,0:08:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a member of\Nthe former Czechoslovakia secret police.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.40,0:08:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.81,0:08:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to know what you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.61,0:08:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I know nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.68,0:08:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Except…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.01,0:08:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.22,0:08:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I've consciously tried to forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.82,0:08:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I have consciously tried to forget\Nabout that mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.16,0:08:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I've never touched\Nor messed with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.83,0:08:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and why it still stands there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.53,0:08:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All the political prisoners\Nwho were brought there
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.50,0:08:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the researchers who were there\Ndisappeared one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.44,0:09:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.08,0:09:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that wall?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.85,0:09:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What wall?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.05,0:09:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The other day, I went inside that mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.09,0:09:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no sign\Nof anyone having entered it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.56,0:09:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's completely abandoned. However,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.96,0:09:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,on the north side of the second floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.47,0:09:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a wall that looks as if it was\Nhastily put up to shut something inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.71,0:09:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I tear down that wall?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.49,0:09:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you frightened of, Captain Ranke?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.36,0:09:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You just might die.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.86,0:09:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If you get any closer to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.33,0:09:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,both you and I…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.77,0:10:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,might see what true fear is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.78,0:11:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz Bonaparta, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.28,0:11:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't heard that name in a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.18,0:11:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you take milk or sugar in your coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.25,0:11:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine black.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.99,0:12:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.26,0:12:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I'm just surprised that a fan\Nof Franz Bonaparta has suddenly shown up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.33,0:12:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard about you from Moravia Publishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.96,0:12:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Sovák,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.40,0:12:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard you were\NMr. Bonaparta's editor for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.37,0:12:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.84,0:12:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was only his editor
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.47,0:12:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,when he worked under\Nthe pen name Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.78,0:12:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to know\Nwhat kind of person he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.58,0:12:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz Bonaparta, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.59,0:12:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He would come to my home here\Nto discuss his work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.36,0:12:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He would sit in that chair there\Njust like you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.57,0:12:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd often play in the garden\Nwith my daughter too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.54,0:12:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But at the time,\Nmy daughter said something odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.24,0:12:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, "That man is frightening."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.31,0:13:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But I doubt\Nmy daughter remembers anything now
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.08,0:13:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,from when she was that young.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.52,0:13:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Was he a member\Nof a government agency then?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.49,0:13:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He probably was.\NI figured he was when I worked with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.26,0:13:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But his demeanor\Nand the way he talked and dressed
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.10,0:13:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,had a gentleness\Nand gracefulness that was uncommon
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.40,0:13:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,among government officials\Nin the old regime.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.77,0:13:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Bonaparta had a doctorate in psychiatry\Nand was also a psychologist.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.81,0:13:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He specialized in neurosurgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.81,0:13:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh… I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.95,0:13:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see, when did I last see him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.46,0:13:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was the summer\Nof either 1981 or 1982.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.43,0:13:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That day, he suddenly dropped by here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.53,0:13:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He talked about his idea for a new book.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.83,0:13:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember now.\NHe appeared rather energetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.57,0:13:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the new story about?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.68,0:14:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It was about a monster who falls in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.41,0:14:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like a mix of Sleeping Beauty\Nand Beauty and the Beast.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.59,0:14:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I rejected it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.39,0:14:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Then just before he left,\Nwhen he was at the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.13,0:14:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,he said, "Oh, I know. How about this?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.73,0:14:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he turned around and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.07,0:14:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,"A story about a door\Nthat must never be opened."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.24,0:14:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked him,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.27,0:14:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,"Is there a paradise beyond it?\NOr does a monster come out?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.64,0:14:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he said,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.51,0:14:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,"No. Since it must never be opened,\NI guess it won't make much of a story."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.85,0:14:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,After saying that, he laughed and left.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.12,0:14:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the last time I saw him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.10,0:15:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you find anything significant\Nabout this Bonaparta guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.07,0:15:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I didn't learn much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.14,0:15:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer, what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.51,0:15:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just admiring the nice weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.52,0:15:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it sure is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.15,0:15:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.19,0:15:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello? Police?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.69,0:15:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Sovák. I live near Schwaig Square.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.43,0:15:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,A man just came to my place
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.00,0:15:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,who I think is wanted as\Na person of interest
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.03,0:15:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in those serial murders in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.94,0:15:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he was Japanese.\NThat neurosurgeon Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.41,0:15:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,JAPANESE DOCTOR IN DÜSSELDORF
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.42,0:15:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Ethanol?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.36,0:15:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It smells like disinfectant.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.72,0:16:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Death… Several people… died here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.09,0:16:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten people…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.23,0:16:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe 20…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.63,0:16:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No, even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.89,0:16:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That woman…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.35,0:17:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,She's the one from the sketchbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.99,0:17:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The mother of those twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.30,0:17:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, if we don't hurry,\Nthe older kids will take the soccer field!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.70,0:17:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up, Milosz!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.44,0:17:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.81,0:17:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Go! Counter attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.18,0:17:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no! Pull back!\NThey're charging for the goal!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.55,0:17:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no! They'll score!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.05,0:17:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.95,0:17:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,-Woah!\N-Milosz!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.69,0:17:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You okay, Milosz?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.32,0:17:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Wake up, Milosz!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.23,0:17:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice save, Milosz!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.23,0:17:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Way to clear it!\NYou stopped them from scoring!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.96,0:17:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,-What?\N-Way to go, Milosz!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.90,0:17:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He's smiling. I guess he's all right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.68,0:17:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.84,0:17:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.05,0:18:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer, aren't you going\Nto talk to Milosz and the other kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.29,0:18:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I figured out why I'm not good at soccer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.60,0:18:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not a team player.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.77,0:18:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens to Detective Jan Suk now?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.14,0:18:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He's wanted as\Na person of interest in the murders,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.71,0:18:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the same as\Nbeing kicked out of society.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.55,0:18:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if he turned himself in,\Nhow could he prove his innocence?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.82,0:18:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How can he prove the existence\Nof this blonde woman who left the scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.06,0:18:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He's in the same situation as you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.19,0:18:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is one difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.17,0:18:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be seeing you, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.67,0:18:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.17,0:18:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,As for these murders,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.54,0:19:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,there is one person who knows\Nall the particulars about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.44,0:19:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He's right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.15,0:19:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What if I sent\Nsomething like this to the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.45,0:19:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.16,0:19:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a letter from a serial murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.39,0:19:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a detailed description of things\Nthat have been kept secret
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.76,0:19:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that only the real murderer could know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.40,0:19:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you send this to the police,\Nthen you'll be arrested!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.54,0:19:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This Grimmer person will\Nsomehow make his way back to Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.78,0:19:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure the police will come after him,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.78,0:19:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but this Grimmer guy\Nwill be able to get away from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.02,0:19:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, he was originally\Nquite a talented spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.09,0:19:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But you'll end up being a suspect\Non the run your whole life!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.76,0:19:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.33,0:19:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, this Grimmer person\Nnever really existed anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.70,0:20:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a person someone forced me to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.94,0:20:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if Grimmer is\Nsuspected of murder all his life,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.94,0:20:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't bother me at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.91,0:20:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do you think\Nof doing things this way, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.11,0:20:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, never mind. Don't tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.15,0:20:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to that rose mansion now,\Naren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.69,0:20:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.96,0:20:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You may finally be close to your goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.66,0:20:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm not so sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.93,0:20:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you wouldn't listen\Nif I told you not to be rash.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.87,0:20:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,However, just don't die.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.94,0:20:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.98,0:20:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Like we promised\Nwhen we crossed the Czech border,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.28,0:20:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,when we meet again somewhere,\Nlet's have a picnic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.72,0:20:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll fish for trout in a beautiful spot…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.62,0:20:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and enjoy good wine and cheese.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.83,0:20:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's meet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.68,0:21:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess from now on,\NI'll always be frightened by that sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.72,0:21:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.89,0:21:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Ow! It hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.86,0:21:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.90,0:21:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong? Let me see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.44,0:21:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.61,0:21:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a scrape.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.81,0:21:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll put some disinfectant on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.22,0:21:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.22,0:22:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a big boy. Tough it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.92,0:22:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There. You're very brave.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.67,0:22:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Kenzo Tenma, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.47,0:22:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We're the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.84,0:22:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Come with us to the station.
